cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper applies a technique called Layer-wise relevance propagation (LRP) to explain the predictions of a convolutional neural network (CNN) trained on a topic categorization task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with non-linear classifiers, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper compares its technique with standard sensitivity analysis, which involves visualizations, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
